               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-355-person2572">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JONES
               <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2572" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2572" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2572" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mr. Light, of <placeName id="t18270913-355-crimeloc1971">Skinner-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-355-crimeloc1971" type="placeName" value="Skinner-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-355-crimeloc1971" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-355-off1969 t18270913-355-crimeloc1971"></join>; he <rs id="t18270913-355-viclabel1972" type="occupation">keeps a Birmingham warehouse</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-355-victim2571 t18270913-355-viclabel1972"></join> - the prisoner came with two others to buy a pin-cushion; they went out, came in again, and wanted another like it, which we had not got - we said we would change the first one - the prisoner then bought a comb, and went away; they came again with a fourth person, who wanted a knife, and while my mistress was gone into the parlour, I saw the prisoner with a gold watch in his hand; he was shutting down the glass-case from which he had taken it; he ran out; I pursued - the others ran after me, and I was tripped up. I do not know what became of the watch - the glass-case was on the counter.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. McDOWELL. Q. Was it not a dark night? A. Yes; I never lost sight of him - my master told me to make quite sure of him.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Do you swear your master told you to swear to him at all events? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-355-person2573">
                  WILLIAM 
                  LIGHT
               <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2573" type="surname" value="LIGHT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2573" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2573" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep this house, it is in the parish of St. Sepulchre. I told my boy he might be asked if he was positive of the prisoner, and to speak accurately to what he knew. I was out at the time - I had seen a gold watch in the case about an hour before.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. What was the lowest value of it? A. The selling price is 7l. 10s. I paid about 6l. 10s. for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-355-person2574">
                  GEORGE 
                  BUSH
               <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2574" type="surname" value="BUSH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2574" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2574" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 13th of September, between eight and nine o'clock at night, I was in Skinner-street - I saw the prisoner come out of this shop; he was running towards King-street, and Jones running after him - three more came out, and ran right before him. Jones fell down - I ran and caught the prisoner - we brought him back to Mr. Light's. Mrs. Light said, "That is the boy who took the watch out of the case."</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Was it not dark? A. There was plenty of gas-light. I found 2s. on him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-355-person2575">
                  GEORGE 
                  GODFREY
               <interp inst="t18270913-355-person2575" type="surname" value="GODFREY"></interp>
